    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-12-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-12-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="133" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d133">
                <head>No. 133.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-12-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 20,
                            1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>All intentions and reports of reestablishing Clarence at Bluefields denied
                        absolutely at foreign office. Sensational attempts are apparent to create
                        misunderstanding and misrepresent relations and intentions of the United
                        States and Great Britain in connection with Nicaraguan, affairs.</p>
            </div>
